{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setHeaderFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"updateHeader"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GtkListBoxUpdateHeaderFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtklistbox.h@T@GtkListBoxUpdateHeaderFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"destroy"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By setting a header function on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"box"},{"type":"text","text":" one can dynamically add headers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in front of rows, depending on the contents of the row and its position"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the list."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For instance, one could use it to add headers in front of the first item"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a new kind, in a list sorted by the kind."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update_header"},{"type":"text","text":" can look at the current header widget using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListBoxRow.get_header"},{"type":"text","text":"] and either update the state of the widget"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as needed, or set a new one using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListBoxRow.set_header"},{"type":"text","text":"]. If no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"header is needed, set the header to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that you may get many calls "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update_header"},{"type":"text","text":" to this for a particular"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"row when e.g. changing things that donâ€™t affect the header. In this case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it is important for performance to not blindly replace an existing header"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with an identical one."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"update_header"},{"type":"text","text":" function will be called for each row after the call,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and it will continue to be called each time a row changes (via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListBoxRow.changed"},{"type":"text","text":"]) and when the row before changes (either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"by [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListBoxRow.changed"},{"type":"text","text":"] on the previous row, or when the previous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"row becomes a different row). It is also called for all rows when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListBox.invalidate_headers"},{"type":"text","text":"] is called."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/listboxref\/setheaderfunc(updateheader:userdata:destroy:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier